      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "This comment threw me off a little. Is this clearer to what is actually happening inside `SetFuzzedEerrNo`?\r\n\r\n```suggestion\r\n    // Have a permanent error at bind_errnos[0] because when the fuzzed data is exhausted\r\n    // SetFuzzedErrNo() will always set the first element. We want to avoid Bind()\r\n    // returning -1 and setting errno to EAGAIN repeatedly.\r\n```",
      "commit_id" : "c2f80ba98d2b4cd8b1ded6f507cd457de05a7884",
      "created_at" : "2022-05-09T16:38:50Z",
      "diff_hunk" : "@@ -160,6 +160,41 @@ int FuzzedSock::Connect(const sockaddr*, socklen_t) const\n     return 0;\n }\n \n+int FuzzedSock::Bind(const sockaddr*, socklen_t) const\n+{\n+    // Have a permanent error at bind_errnos[0] because when the fuzzed data is exhausted\n+    // SetFuzzedErrNo() will always return the first element and we want to avoid Bind()\n+    // returning -1 and setting errno to EAGAIN repeatedly.",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/24378#discussion_r868207821",
